Continuous Authorization

Instead of checking access only at login, ARTH.OS should continuously evaluate trust throughout a user's session.

Examples:

User logs in from Kerala → normal access.
Thirty minutes later, high-risk financial operations begin from a new device → increase authentication requirements.
AI agent starts issuing unusual API requests → throttle or isolate the agent.
Privileged administrator attempts actions outside normal patterns → require step-up approval or terminate the session.

This "continuous trust" model is significantly more advanced than traditional role-based systems and aligns with modern Zero Trust security architectures.

